If you’re refused planning permission, ask your local planning authority (LPA) why. You can then make changes to your application and send it in again. 

As a last resort, if you think the LPA’s decision is unreasonable, you can [appeal.](http://www.planningportal.gov.uk/planning/appeals/online/makeanappeal "Planning Portal: make an appeal"){:rel="external"}

*[LPA]: local planning authority
